<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Ellampus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ellampus mordvilkoi" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mordvilkoi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Ellampus mordvilkoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shows the main characteristics of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Abeille de Perrin, 1879" authorityName="Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Philoctetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Philoctetes sensu" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sensu">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Philoctetes sensu</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Kimsey, LS" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" refId="B56" refString="Kimsey, LS, Bohart, RM, 1991. The Chrysidid Wasps of the World. Oxford University Press, New York" title="The Chrysidid Wasps of the World." year="1991">Kimsey and Bohart (1991)</bibRefCitation>
. The gena is not bisected by the genal carina, the punctuation on the mesosoma is more distributed along the notauli and the anal margin of the last metasomal tergite has a distinct brownish transparent rim with a wide median notch. Therefore, we have moved this taxon into the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Abeille de Perrin, 1879" authorityName="Abeille de Perrin" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Philoctetes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Philoctetes" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Philoctetes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Abeille.
</paragraph>
